<subSubSection pageId="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1534,1882]" pageId="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1823,1847]" pageId="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[525,626,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="20">cinctutus</emphasis>
(meaning girded, enclosed, encircled as though by a belt or band), an allusion to the numerous, fine, granulated, horizontal epithecal bands that encircle the corallum.
</paragraph>
